reviews.review: this is now my new favorite Star Wars movie.....LOVED IT

I really don't understand the hate this movie is getting? It was really good and after seeing it a second time, it may be my new favorite. Hating on the Star Wars movies has become a new industry on the internet. I have watched a ton of "plot hole" complaint videos on YouTube, and after just watching it a second time, they can almost all be explained with relative ease.
It is a bad movie. Without soul, made without talent, who end of the worst way, 40 years of a subculture of endearing characters and stories. A big disappoint.

The critics are simply wrong about this one. I'm 41 years old and a fan of the original trilogy first and foremost, but I'm not one of those rabid, reactionary fans who seem determined to hate anything new. I had some problems with 7 and 8, but largely liked them. This 9th film is by far the best of the sequel trilogy, and I don't know how it could have been executed better.

I had concerns about the film going in, but they proved to be unfounded. Considering the 8 films that proceed this one, I just don't know how it could have been wrapped up any better.

The movie is fun, it has heart, it answers questions, and it's the satisfying conclusion that Star Wars deserves.
The movie was really great , the only down thing is that it was compacted , but definitely a MUST WATCH
It was a awesome movie had a good time with my bro

It’s definitely the best movie of the newest trilogy, although there’s maybe 30-45 minutes of stuff anybody would wanna see. A lot of filler and could’ve had 20-30 mins edited out to make a more solid movie. Go in knowing the good guys when like EVERY Star Wars movies and expect good effects with a mediocre story with a lot of plot holes.

While enjoyable it still felt like a mess trying to make up for the faults of Ep.8.
STAR WARS goes out with a Try-Hard-Meh.

It just feels like an unrewarding ending to a trilogy that feels like a big waste of time. You know the original star wars gave you this big interesting universe to fantasize about and while not great the prequels gave you new themes amd possibilties? The new trilogy does none of that. I feel like I just to pretend this trilogy never happened and go back to the legends stories.

The best of the sequels! 
6th best star wars movie overall!
